name: La Pambelé
description: La Pambelé es la orquesta de salsa que está sorprendiendo a la escena de la música por interpretar la salsa que se hacía en las décadas de los 70 (o salsa brava) con letras que narran la actualidad. Canciones con sabor nostálgico pero actuales o como tituló un medio colombiano: “una nueva apuesta por la salsa vieja”. Sus canciones ya han sido interpretadas en vivo en Salsa al Parque o el Teatro Colsubsidio. Sus canciones suenan regularmente en la programación de Radio Nacional de Colombia y la emisora antioqueña especializada en salsa Latina Stereo; la industria musical reconoce su nombre gracias a sus showcases en Circulart (Medellín), Bime Bogotá y Bogotá Music Market. En 2022 publicaron su disco debut titulado Primer Round, el cual les permitió darse a conocer y llevar al mercado global dos vinilos. En sus influencias resaltan nombres como Markolino Dimond, Eddie Palmieri, Edy Martínez, El Pantera, Ismael Miranda, Quintana, Rivera, entre otros. La Pambelé is the salsa orchestra that is surprising the music scene by performing salsa from the 70s (or heavy guaguanco) with lyrics that narrate contemporary issues. Their songs have a nostalgic yet current flavor, or as a Colombian media outlet described them: “a new take on old salsa.” Their songs have already been performed live at Salsa al Parque and the Teatro Colsubsidio. Their songs are regularly played on Radio Nacional de Colombia and the Antioquian salsa radio station Latina Stereo. The music industry recognizes their name thanks to their showcases at Circulart (Medellín), Bime Bogotá, and Bogotá Music Market. In 2022, they released their debut album titled Primer Round, which allowed them to make a name for themselves and bring two vinyl records to the global market. Their influences include names like Markolino Dimond, Eddie Palmieri, Edy Martínez, El Pantera, Ismael Miranda, Quintana, Rivera, among others.

name: Ministerio del beat
description: Somos Bruno Mondora (voz) Nahuel Aloisio (voz) Julián Martin Avellaneda (bajo, voz y composición) Ema Garraza (guitarra) Marcos Navarrete (percusión) Clara Zivano (batería) y Andrés Mora (teclado y voz) Mezclamos funk, hip hop, lofi y rock.

name: Semblanzas del río Guapi
description: Semblanzas del río Guapi´s music portrays the enchantment of a place in the South Pacific coast of Colombia where the magic of endless rivers, pristine jungles, mangroves and the fury of the ocean collide. Listening to the all female choir leading the percussion and marimba de chonta ensemble takes you to a mystical territory where ancestry, religious syncretism and survival blend into a unique music that reminds us what life is about. Semblanzas del río Guapi´s music is medicine for the soul. Semblanzas del río Guapi is not a new name for the people immersed in marimba de chonta music, their sound is cult for those who have connected to this thriving music scene. The bambuco, juga, patacoré, currulao, cantos de boga, bunde and pasion rhythms collected in Voy pa allá, Semblanzas del río Guapi´s new record, takes you to a journey to connect with the heart and soul of the Pacific region jungles of Guapi and Limones in Cauca - Colombia, in the sound and strenght of a young band. An ensemble that has received, like no other, the knowledge from the elders and has preserved the original sound of this deep mysterious music to take it to the future. ESP. Maestría. Semblanzas del Río Guapi es pura maestría. Esta agrupación que se creó en el 2009 en honor a su río —arteria principal y columna vertebral del territorio—, es hoy una de las más reconocidas de la región. Sus voces retumban en la selva guapireña, invitan a conocerla, preservarla y comprender las raíces de su tradición.

name: Isósceles
description: Isosceles are a Scottish indie pop band formed in Glasgow, Scotland. The band is composed of Jack Valentine (Guitar & Vocals), William Aikman (Keyboards & Vocals), Andrew Wilson (Bass) and Bobby Duff (Drums). Formed in 2006 for a one-off gig, the band began playing gigs around Glasgow and recording songs which would eventually be played by Vic Galloway on Radio One. This exposure resulted in the Leeds-based independent record label Art Goes Pop offering to release "Get Your Hands Off / I Go" in 2007. Alex Kapranos from Franz Ferdinand was at the single launch and asked Isosceles to support them on a tour of the Scottish Highlands including gigs in Inverness, Fort William, Dundee and Portree. At the start of 2008 they began their first tour of England before releasing their second single "Kitch Bitch" / "Watertight" in April. Further gigs in England were followed by appearances at Glastonbury and T In The Park. In September 2008, the band played at the Venice Biennale of Architecture in Venice. Isosceles continued to play around Glasgow, with the band supporting Correcto, Clinic, The Vaselines and Shonen Knife.

name: Organicways
description: Organicways es una banda de Indie Rock de San José Costa Rica que comenzó solo 3 meses antes de que la pandemia azotara al mundo. Con el deseo de comunicar y crear a través de la música, este grupo de amigos lanzó un sencillo “The old man ” y un EP “What you don’t know”. A lo largo de su aventura han logrado tocar en varios escenarios de Costa Rica, compartiendo escenario con colegas de la escena "Nicotine Rush", lanzada el 16 de febrero de 2024, constituye el tercer sencillo de nuestro álbum debut 'Outside Reality.' (Será lanzado en el 2024) Esta canción es una estimulante fusión de vibraciones del surf rock, armonías espaciales y un ritmo de sintetizador contagioso. ------------------------------------------------- Organicways is an Indie Rock band from San José, Costa Rica, which started just 3 months before the pandemic hit the world. With the desire to communicate and create through music, this group of friends released a single "The Old Man" and an EP "What You Don't Know." Throughout their journey, they have managed to perform on various stages in Costa Rica, sharing the stage with many bands from the independent scene... Nicotine Rush," released on February 16, 2024, serves as the third single from our debut album 'Outside Reality.' (which will be relese in 2024) This song is an invigorating fusion of surf rock vibes, spacey harmonies, and infectious synth rhythm. Side projects: Asael Guevara Lead Singer and Solo Artist.

name: Luz María Cardenal
description: One Woman Band + Livelooping + First Female Chapman Stick Player in Mexico Luz María Cardenal es cineasta, cantautora, multi-instrumentista y es la primera mujer stickista en México. Interpreta en solitario música llena de sensibilidad y fuerza haciendo livelooping con letras que hablan de la naturaleza, el amor y el ser, teniendo en sus canciones segmentos instrumentales con influencias que van desde los soundtracks, el pop, el rock progresivo, folk, hip-hop; y con instrumentos como la flauta transversal, guitarras, chapman-stick, beatbox, piano, silbidosy que en vivo interpreta estilo one-woman band. Una artista mexicana y multidisciplinaria que ha abierto conciertos de la cantante Lila Downs, ha realizado colaboraciones con músicos de Egipto y que continúa creciendo y produciendo música y cine.

name: Radio Bemba
description: Radio Bemba es un dúo colaborativo que produce ideas y distintos géneros musicales sin límites.

name: Johnny Garso
description: Johnny Garso estará presentando su nuevo álbum “Espada y Rosa hasta que muera” en lo que será la primera gira del artista zaragozano cantando en directo los temas de su último trabajo en español. Estamos ante un disco de 13 cortes cargado de emociones, distorsión y un toque moderno, que da como resultado un sonido actual con un profundo aroma de nostalgia. En el podremos ver desde su faceta más íntima, con guitarra y voz desnuda, hasta la expresión visceral y reivindicativa de la banda completa. Pero donde Johnny muestra verdaderamente su esencia, pasión, energía y mensaje, es en el escenario, con un directo arrollador que no deja indiferente a nadie. Ante un panorama donde se necesitan nuevos referentes, Johnny Garso está aquí para liderar una escena joven, poderosa y duradera en nuestro país. El Espada y Rosa Tour, es una celebración de lo emocional y lo frenético.

name: Alvaro Ruiz Oficial
description: Fashion forward Puerto Rican urban-alt rapper, Álvaro Díaz, is having the biggest moment of his career. In 2023, he received 10 diamond, platinum & gold certifications for his debut album Felicilandia, sold-out shows all over Latin America & Spain with over 100k fans in attendance and surpassed 650M global streams. He made his debut at the Coca-Cola Music Hall in Puerto Rico with 12k fans in attendance, received nominations from Premio Lo Nuestro, Rolling Stone en Español & Premios Juventud, was featured in Tainy’s album DATA on “Paranormal,” and wrote the songs “Gucci Los Paños” for Karol G & “Panties y Brasieres” for Rauw Alejandro. In 2024, Díaz won a Europe Music Video Award and on May 17th released his sophomore album Sayonara which debuted at #1 in US Latin albums & Top 20 in US General Market on Apple Music, debuted #2 on Spotify’s Top Albums Debut Global Chart, #8 on Billboard’s Latin Rhythms Albums & #14 on Top Latin Albums amassing +310M global streams. The focus track “GATITAS SANDUNGUERAS VOL. 1,” feat. FEID, debuted at #34 on Billboard’s Hot Latin Songs. Currently, Díaz is on the cover of Rolling Stone Español, was nominated for a Premios HEAT. Catch Álvaro Díaz on tour this year in Spain in the summer and Latin America and the US in the fall.

name: Lαɱααɾ
description: Lamaar is a singer and songwriter with Italian roots living in Andalusia. Her music mixes her soulful and bluesy voice with her intense love for latin, traditional and folk music, from flamenco to balkan music, from latino-American music to blues and soul. Lamaar started singing as soon as she was able to talk, but she founded her first rock band with her brother , the guitarist Marco Picaro, at the age of 15. In 2013 the two siblings founded the Rock Blues band Ramrod with which they started writing original music and touring Italy and Europe. Lamaar is the front-woman and songwriter of Ramrod and she has currently released two albums : "First Fall" and "Jet Black". In 2020 Lamaar feels that it's time to share her inner and hidden universe with the rest of the world, that's when she decides to start her solo project. Lamaar simply gives voice to her soul, without filters and limitations, mixing the musical genres that formed her.
